---
const stats = [
  { value: '40+', label: 'Brands collaborated with' },
  { value: '2', label: 'Core niches: tech & home' },
  { value: '24h', label: 'Average response time' },
];
---

<section id="about" class="px-6 py-24 sm:py-32 lg:px-12">
  <div class="mx-auto grid max-w-6xl grid-cols-1 items-center gap-16 lg:grid-cols-2">
    <!-- Photo -->
    <div class="order-1 lg:order-none">
      <div class="aspect-[4/5] w-full overflow-hidden rounded-3xl bg-stone shadow-sm">
        <img
          src="https://placehold.co/640x800/e8e4dc/1f1d1a?text=Garrett"
          alt="Garrett, UGC creator"
          class="h-full w-full object-cover"
          loading="lazy"
        />
      </div>
    </div>

    <!-- Copy -->
    <div>
      <p class="text-sm font-semibold tracking-wide text-clay uppercase">About Me</p>

      <h2
        class="mt-4 font-[family-name:var(--font-display)] text-4xl leading-tight font-medium text-ink sm:text-5xl"
      >
        Hi, I'm Garrett.
      </h2>

      <p class="mt-6 text-lg leading-relaxed text-charcoal/80">
        I've spent the last few years learning what makes people stop
        scrolling — and turning that into content for brands who need their
        product to feel less like an ad and more like a recommendation from
        a friend.
      </p>

      <p class="mt-4 text-lg leading-relaxed text-charcoal/80">
        My focus is split between two worlds: <span class="font-medium text-ink"
          >tech and apps</span
        >, where I make complex products feel simple and exciting, and
        <span class="font-medium text-ink">home and lifestyle</span>, where I
        show products doing what they do best — making everyday life a
        little easier.
      </p>

      <p class="mt-4 text-lg leading-relaxed text-charcoal/80">
        Brands work with me because I don't just shoot content — I think
        like a marketer. Every video is built to hold attention, build
        trust, and move someone from "interesting" to "I want that."
      </p>

      <!-- Stats -->
      <div class="mt-10 grid grid-cols-3 gap-6 border-t border-stone pt-8">
        {
          stats.map((stat) => (
            <div>
              <p class="font-[family-name:var(--font-display)] text-3xl font-medium text-ink">
                {stat.value}
              </p>
              <p class="mt-1 text-sm text-charcoal/60">{stat.label}</p>
            </div>
          ))
        }
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>
